getevtlen

public static long getevtlen(long ehandle)
                      throws JVRException
sr_getevtlen. Windows Only.

Since the value returned by this function is only valid within the scope of the original signal handler, you probably do not want to call this function directly. Instead, register as an event listener jvr.addEventListener(net.threebit.jvr.MetaEventListener).

Throws:
JVRException - if there is no current event to report on.

getevtdata

public static java.lang.Object getevtdata(long ehandle)
                                   throws JVRException
sr_getevtdatap. Windows Only.

Note that the "p" has been dropped in the method name since in Java we do not return a pointer.

An Object is returned because depending on the type of event, several different cases are possible. The JVR event dispatcher will handle each return value.

Throws:
JVRException
